description.plain:
Quavious Keyate Marshall (born April 2, 1991), known professionally as Quavo, is an American rapper and record producer, one third of Atlanta hip-hop group Migos alongside Takeoff and Offset.

Quavo’s individual career was initiated by a series of guest features for acclaimed hip-hop artists like Travis Scott, Young Thug, A$AP Ferg, Post Malone and DJ Khaled. On December 21, 2017 he released a collaboration album with Travis Scott called Huncho Jack, Jack Huncho. He released his debut solo album QUAVO HUNCHO on October 11, 2018.

songs.title: HUNCHO DREAMS

description.plain:
“HUNCHO DREAMS” is Quavo’s response to Nicki Minaj’s “Barbie Dreams.” Nicki specifically name-dropped Quavo on the song, rapping:

Somebody go and make sure Karrueche okay though
I heard she think I’m tryna give the coochie to Quavo

This song seemingly confirms that Quavo and Nicki have had a romantic relationship at some point. Rumors of the two being romantically linked began when they were spotted together at Coachella in April 2018. These rumors were reinvigorated in July 2018, after the two appeared together on Ella Mai’s “Boo’d Up (Remix).”

In 2017, the two collaborated on “She for Keeps” and “Motorsport,” which are both mentioned directly and indirectly on this song.

Additionally, in what perhaps may have been intentional, “HUNCHO DREAMS” is the third song on QUAVO HUNCHO, just as “Barbie Dreams” is the third track on Queen.

songs.full_title: FLIP THE SWITCH by Quavo (Ft. Drake)
songs.title: FLIP THE SWITCH

description.plain:
“FLIP THE SWITCH” is a collaboration between Quavo and Drake. The song’s title is likely taken from a lyric on Drake’s “Nonstop”:

Look, I just flipped a switch (flipped, flipped)

The song’s chorus interpolates “Ha” by Juvenile.

Quavo has previously collaborated with Drake both independently and collectively with Migos. The song also arrives in the midst of the “Aubrey & The Three Migos” Tour.

Days before this song was released, GQ released a video featuring Quavo in which he alluded to a possible collaborative mixtape between Migos and Drake.

songs.title: WORKIN ME

description.plain:
On “WORKIN ME,” Quavo raps about his woman’s ability to seduce and entice him. He also brags about his lavish lifestyle and makes numerous references to sports and pop culture. The song is produced by Murda Beatz and Sool Got Hits.

“WORKIN ME” is one of three singles Quavo released on August 10, 2018, alongside “LAMB TALK” and “BUBBLE GUM.” All of these singles were released two days before the kickoff of the “Aubrey & The Three Migos Tour,” Drake and Migos‘ co-headlining stadium tour.
